#: ../../os_updates.rst:5
msgid "Operating system updates"
msgstr ""

#: ../../os_updates.rst:7
msgid ""
"NethServer 8 is installed on top of GNU/Linux distributions and tries to "
"preserve default configuration as much as possible. It's up to the system"
" administrator to choose how the operating system updates are applied."
msgstr ""

#: ../../os_updates.rst:10
msgid ""
"Usually, it's a good practice to apply security updates as soon as "
"possible. But, even if NethServer depends on few packages, not all system"
" administrators feel confident about automatic updates."
msgstr ""

#: ../../os_updates.rst:13
msgid "Please, take a look to your distribution documentation:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../os_updates.rst:15
msgid ""
"`Rocky Linux/AlmaLinux "
"<https://docs.rockylinux.org/guides/security/dnf_automatic/>`_"
msgstr ""

#: ../../os_updates.rst:16
msgid "`Debian <https://wiki.debian.org/UnattendedUpgrades>`_"
msgstr ""

#: ../../os_updates.rst:20
msgid ""
"It's not recommended to enable automatic updates on CentOS Stream, since "
"it is considered a preview of next RHEL stable release. Updates could "
"bring major releases of podman and SELinux policies introducing "
"unexpected bugs."
msgstr ""

